<i>♪ got the music in you.</i>

11:38.699 --> 11:43.168
<i>♪ find you've got the music</i>
<i>got the music in you. ♪</i>

11:43.170 --> 11:45.770
<i>♪ ohh!</i>

11:45.772 --> 11:49.808
♪ everypony says that you should
<i>learn to express your voice ♪</i>

11:49.810 --> 11:52.343
<i>♪ but if talk doesn't</i>
<i>seem like it's the answer ♪</i>

11:52.345 --> 11:59.284
<i>♪ when you find you've got the</i>
<i>music, got the music in you. ♪</i>

11:59.286 --> 12:02.320
<i>♪ find you've got</i>
<i>the music in you. ♪</i>

12:02.322 --> 12:08.493
<i>♪ got the music, got</i>
<i>the music in you. ♪</i>

12:08.495 --> 12:17.168
<i>(cheers)</i>

12:17.170 --> 12:20.004
Pony tones! Pony tones!

12:23.442 --> 12:27.145
<i>(galloping)</i>

12:27.147 --> 12:28.446
Pony tones!

12:28.448 --> 12:31.182
That was truly amazing!

12:31.184 --> 12:34.018
And you sounded better
than ever, big brother!

12:34.020 --> 12:36.087
(snort)

12:36.089 --> 12:38.456
Fluttershy, you were on the
wrong side of the curtain!

12:38.458 --> 12:40.291
You totally missed the show!

12:42.328 --> 12:45.830
Just like a true professional,
fluttershy was back stage

12:45.832 --> 12:48.333
Making sure everything
ran smoothly.

12:48.335 --> 12:50.835
And it was perfect!

12:50.837 --> 12:53.438
That was fantastic, pony tones.

12:53.440 --> 12:56.975
My new puppy and I thought it
was super duper crazy good!

12:56.977 --> 12:58.443
Why, thank you!

13:02.014 --> 13:04.082
